[{"id":"VR188357","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR188355.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following is a correct statement about the fusion reaction?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR188357_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">Fusion reactions in stars produce photons. One of these reactions can be represented by the equation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 particles of H with mass number 1 and atomic number 1, reacts to produce, H e with mass number 4 and atomic number 2, plus, 2 particles of lowercase e with mass number 0 and atomic number 1, plus 2 nu particles, plus 2 gamma particles\"><math alttext=\"4 particles of H with mass number 1 and atomic number 1, reacts to produce, H e with mass number 4 and atomic number 2, plus, 2 particles of lowercase e with mass number 0 and atomic number 1, plus 2 nu particles, plus 2 gamma particles\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow><msubsup><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup><mtext>H</mtext><mo>→</mo><mmultiscripts><mrow><mtext>He</mtext></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mmultiscripts><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>ν</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>γ</mi></mrow></math></span></span> , where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H\"><math alttext=\"H\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is a hydrogen nucleus, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H e\"><math alttext=\"H e\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>He</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is a helium nucleus, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"nu\"><math alttext=\"nu\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow><mi>ν</mi></mrow></math></span></span> is a neutrino, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"gamma\"><math alttext=\"gamma\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>γ</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is a photon, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase e with mass number 0 and atomic number 1\"><math alttext=\"lowercase e with mass number 0 and atomic number 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mmultiscripts><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is a positron.</p></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mass of the reactants is equal to the mass of the products because mass is conserved.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The mass of the reactants is greater than the mass of the products because fusion creates a larger atom.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The total mass-energy of the reactants is equal to the total mass-energy of the products because of conservation of mass-energy.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The total mass-energy of the reactants is greater than the total mass-energy of the products because photons are released in the process.</p>"],"answer":2}]